description.plain: Casada Aaron Sorrell (born November 17, 1992 in Detroit, Michigan), is an American rapper best known for his songs “Bloxk Party” with Drego and “Whole Lotta Choppas” which received a remix from Nicki Minaj.

songs.title: Bloxk Party

description.plain: Detroit rappers Sada Baby and Drego trade bars over a Von Jose produced beat in “Bloxk Party”, the 19th track from Sada Baby’s 2019 album “Bartier Bounty”, and the fifth track on Drego and Beno’s album “Sorry for the get off”. The track was released as a single, and blew up to become Sada Baby and Drego’s most popular track.

songs.full_title: Whole Lotta Choppas (Remix) by Sada Baby (Ft. Nicki Minaj)
songs.title: Whole Lotta Choppas (Remix)

description.plain:
After a two-month social media hiatus, Nicki came back online to announce her feature on the remix of TikTok’s viral original song, “Whole Lotta Choppas.”

On the song, Nicki raps on her motherhood, sexual desires, and luxuries, while Sada converts the same lyrics from the original.

Not only does this song mark the artist’s first collaboration with each other, but also marks Nicki’s first track after her accouchement. Alongside revealing this track’s release, she posted a sentiment on Instagram to give more insight on her baby.
